From: OpenWrt Port
Subject: [PATCH] Makefile: fix $< expanding to FORCE when generating environment.h

Append FORCE to the end of the $(env_h) dependency list, ensuring the
first prerequisite is always include/generated/env.in. This prevents $<
in cmd_gen_envt from incorrectly expanding to the FORCE phony target,
which caused the build error:
  /bin/sh: 1: cannot open FORCE: No such file

This follows U-Boot kbuild convention: real source files first,
FORCE phony target last in the dependency list.
---
 Makefile | 2 +-
 1 file changed, 1 insertion(+), 1 deletion(-)

diff --git a/Makefile b/Makefile
--- a/Makefile
+++ b/Makefile
@@ -2105,7 +2105,7 @@ quiet_cmd_gen_envt = ENVT    $@
       cmd_gen_envt = \
 	awk -f $(srctree)/scripts/env2string.awk $< >$@
 
-$(env_h): include/generated/env.in
+$(env_h): include/generated/env.in FORCE
 	$(call cmd,gen_envt)
